C. Model Inversion and Extraction Attacks
1) Understanding Model Inversion: Model inversion attacks aim to reconstruct sensitive input data from the outputs of an LLM [12]. This is a significant privacy concern, especially when models are trained on confidential or personal data [13].
Mechanism:
• Repeated Querying: The attacker sends numerous inputs and collects outputs [14] • Statistical Analysis: Uses outputs to infer patterns and reconstruct inputs [15] • Reconstruction of Training Data: Potentially revealing sensitive information [16]
2) Model Extraction Techniques: Model extraction attacks involve replicating an LLM’s functionality by observing its inputs and outputs [17]. This allows attackers to create a surrogate model without access to the original model’s parameters [18].
Implications:
• Intellectual Property Theft: Unauthorized replication of proprietary models [19]
