A. Architecture Overview
The proposed framework comprises several interconnected components designed to monitor, evaluate, and respond to potential threats in real-time. This section provides a detailed overview of the system’s architecture, data flow, and integration points.
1) System Components:
• Trust Scoring Engine: Calculates dynamic trust scores based on predefined metrics, assessing the legitimacy of incoming queries.
• Cascading Validation Layers: Sequential validation mechanisms that scrutinize queries for potential threats through multiple layers of analysis.
• Adaptive Response Module: Adjusts system behavior dynamically based on trust scores and detected threat levels, implementing measures such as throttling or restricting access.
• Alert and Notification System: Generates alerts and notifies administrators of detected threats, enabling prompt responses to potential security incidents.
