B. Dynamic Trust Scoring
The Trust Scoring Engine is the cornerstone of the defense framework, responsible for evaluating the trustworthiness of incoming queries. By leveraging multiple trust metrics, it assigns a dynamic trust score that informs subsequent validation and response actions. 1) Trust Metrics: The trust score is computed based on three primary metrics: 1) Query Pattern Analysis: Examines the structural and syntactical patterns of the query to identify suspicious or anomalous structures. 2) Content Similarity Scoring: Assesses the similarity of the query content against a repository of known benign and malicious queries using semantic analysis.
3) Historical Behavior Analysis: Monitors user interactions over time to detect deviations from established behavioral norms.
2) Mathematical Formulation: The trust score T is calculated using the following weighted sum of the individual trust metrics:
T = w1 × P + w2 × S + w3 × H (1)
